# Banned attribution (local reference only)

Before `git commit` or `git push` in Perpetua-Tools:

1. Read **`.cursor/private/banned-attribution-local.md`** and **`.cursor/private/banned-attribution-patterns`** (gitignored — not on GitHub).
2. If missing, run: `bash scripts/cursor/install-user-git-environment.sh`
3. **Never** copy banned tokens into tracked files (`docs/LESSONS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`, instincts, or commit messages).
4. Approved **primary author** only: `cyre` + owner emails, or `Codex <codex@openai.com>`.

Public policy (no banned-token examples): `../orama-system/docs/wiki/08-git-hygiene-and-branching.md`
